      "content": "The focus in advanced sports genetics is more on specific genes, like *ACTN3*, than broad racial categories, as these genes are distributed across various populations. Some individuals with the *ACTN3* R allele, which is often associated with splicing efficiency in fast-twitch fibers, dominate sprinting. Similarly, body composition and biomechanical efficiencies are shaped by genetics interacting with activity, not by ancestry alone. When designing a framework, focus on movement quality, maximizing their current genetic strengths, and respecting the principle of individual variability over generalized racial predispositions.",
